The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 2: The government today restored benefits under the duty entitlement pass book (depb) scheme to the export of cement. Export of cement shall be entitled for depb benefit with immediate effect, a directorate general of foreign trade notice said here. Only last week the government had lifted the ban on cement exports on expectations of demand slackening in the ensuing monsoon period and the easing of prices in the domestic market.                             
	 New Delhi, June 2: The Dabur group will enter the non-life insurance sector in alliance with the US-based general insurer Liberty Mutual Group to cash in on the rapidly growing income of the countrys middle class.                            
	 Mumbai, June 2: Global financial conglomerate, ING has appointed former Sebi chairman M. Damodaran as chief representative and advisor for ING in India.                             
	 Srinagar, June 2: Steel Authority of India Ltd (SAIL) will open a Rs 300-crore plant at Pulwama. Construction of the steel plant will begin as soon as SAIL bags a no-objection certificate from the pollution control board of the J amp;K government.                            
	 New Delhi, June 2: As many as 8 million telephone connections, including both wireline and wireless, were added in April this year against 10.4 million in March, taking the total number of subscriptions to 308.51 million.                                                                                                                         
